1
00:00:00,083 --> 00:00:03,166
Interviewer: Tell us how you got out, the method and the form of your release

2
00:00:03,875 --> 00:00:05,708
I signed a pledge

3
00:00:05,791 --> 00:00:07,708
Interviewer: What did the pledge stipulate, what did you commit to?

4
00:00:07,875 --> 00:00:09,666
A pledge that if I was caught committing violations

5
00:00:09,875 --> 00:00:12,625
Like skipping prayer and the like, then my punishment would be tripled

6
00:00:13,416 --> 00:00:16,458
For now that’s what they decided for me—later we don’t know what they’ll decide

7
00:00:16,875 --> 00:00:19,750
Your situation becomes frightening later if they catch you a second time

8
00:00:20,708 --> 00:00:24,791
And anyone who goes in to them becomes monitored afterward, and they know everything about him

9
00:00:26,291 --> 00:00:30,083
Interviewer: When you left, were your deposited belongings complete, or did they take anything?

10
00:00:30,625 --> 00:00:31,625
No, no

11
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,875
I had only a ring, a watch, and a phone, and I took them

12
00:00:36,416 --> 00:00:37,416
Nothing was missing?

13
00:00:37,625 --> 00:00:40,791
No, no, my belongings were in an envelope and my name was written on it

14
00:00:40,875 --> 00:00:42,458
Interviewer: Did they take you home, or did they leave you here?

15
00:00:42,541 --> 00:00:45,708
No, no, they took me to the street and left me

16
00:00:46,708 --> 00:00:48,000
They didn’t use this method with you?

17
00:00:48,125 --> 00:00:50,416
No, no, they left me at 11 p.m.

18
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:52,750
Interviewer: Did you know that you would be released that day? Witness: No

19
00:00:53,666 --> 00:00:55,125
Interviewer: Did you find out directly and suddenly?

20
00:00:55,208 --> 00:00:56,666
Suddenly, before you know it, he’s calling

21
00:00:56,875 --> 00:01:00,833
I told you, sometimes two come and call someone to take him; they might not bring him back, or they might bring him back

22
00:01:01,208 --> 00:01:02,208
Or they transfer him somewhere else

23
00:01:02,625 --> 00:01:07,375
Interviewer: From the moment they took you out of the room until they took you out of the prison

24
00:01:08,083 --> 00:01:11,916
Were your hands tied, or were you free when they took you out?

25
00:01:12,083 --> 00:01:15,583
When they release you, they only blindfold you until you reach the start of the street

26
00:01:15,666 --> 00:01:17,125
They remove the blindfold and tell you–Go

27
00:01:19,291 --> 00:01:24,166
Interviewer: Tell me about the moment when you met your mother and your wife

28
00:01:24,291 --> 00:01:27,375
And they met you after you had been missing for a long time, and they didn’t know what had happened to you

29
00:01:28,083 --> 00:01:30,666
How did you handle this situation, and how did they receive you?

30
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:32,958
By God, it was an indescribable feeling

31
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,083
Something indescribable

32
00:01:35,125 --> 00:01:36,958
Is your mother alive? Witness: Yes, thank God

33
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Interviewer: How did they receive you?

34
00:01:38,458 --> 00:01:41,583
The situation at home was like hell

35
00:01:42,958 --> 00:01:46,666
They didn’t know my fate—one person would tell them one thing, and another would tell them I was detained

36
00:01:46,791 --> 00:01:48,791
And another says they killed him, and another says they threw him into Khafsa

37
00:01:48,916 --> 00:01:51,416
And another says they will execute them

38
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:55,583
So whenever someone is executed, they start thinking about me

39
00:01:55,666 --> 00:01:56,916
So my family’s minds are all scattered
